root: ^"Start right there, the north star, right at the end of the little dipper."
^"It's beautiful. I wish we could see this in the city." says Annie.
^"Just another reason to go camping again right?"
^Annie ignores his question. "I didn't know big dipper was a part of that bear one."
^"Read about em a few months. I'll come out here–not here here, but nearby–and practiced. Learned them in school didn't you?"
^"It's a lot easier in class. There's Leo I think."
^"Let me see... yup there it is galloping along."
^"Wow, didn't have till morning. Night Annie."
